observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Inventory Committee to conduct the actual physical count of the Municipality’s property and prepare the RPCPPE;
b. Property Custodian-Designate to ensure that all PPE counted by the Inventory Committee are issued with PAR and provided with PC which should be regularly updated;
c. Municipal Accountant to maintain PPELC; and
d. Municipal Accountant and Property Custodian-Designate to reconcile the accounting and property records.
We further recommended that the Municipal Mayor constantly monitor the status of physical inventory taking to ensure completion and submission of complete RPCPPE within the deadline.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Municipal Accountant and Property Custodian-Designate to strictly comply with the regulations on proper accounting and management of all supplies and materials to have a reliable balance of inventories and related expenses accounts and to safeguard the same against misappropriation;
b. Property Custodian-Designate and department heads to ensure that all accountable forms, medical, dental and agricultural supplies are properly accounted for and to submit regularly the RIS and SSMI to the Property Custodian for consolidation;
c. Municipal Treasurer, Municipal Health Officer and Municipal Agriculturist to submit regularly to Property Custodian the RIS forms, medical, dental and agricultural supplies, respectively, for consolidation to SSMI.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer (MDRRMO) to carefully study the feasibility of the projects before inclusion in the LDRRMP;
b. MDRRMO to facilitate the immediate and completion of the crucial programs/projects/activities (PPAs) of DRRMF within the budget year in order to be adequately prepared for any upcoming disaster/calamity and hence reduce its risk;
c. MDRRMO to submit to the Audit Team the Monthly Report on the Sources and Utilization of DRRM on or before the 15th day after the end of each month through the LDRRM Council (LDRRMC) and the LDC in compliance with Item 5.1.5 of COA Circular No. 2012-002;
d. MDRRMO and LDRRMC to prepare the supplemental LDRRMP for CY 2020 for the total amount of P5,552,378.86 continued to CY 2020 which is allegedly for re-planning; and
e. LDRRMC to regularly monitor and evaluate the implementation of the LDRRMP.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Inventory Committee to conduct the actual physical count of the Municipality’s property and prepare the RPCPPE;
b. Property Custodian-Designate to ensure that all PPE counted by the Inventory Committee are issued with PAR and provided with PC which should be regularly updated;
c. Municipal Accountant to maintain PPELC; and
d. Municipal Accountant and Property Custodian-Designate to reconcile the accounting and property records.
We further recommended that the Municipal Mayor constantly monitor the status of physical inventory taking to ensure completion and submission of complete RPCPPE within the deadline.

