observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Municipal Accountant in coordination with the BAC Chairman to submit the lacking documents to the Audit Team for evaluation;
b. Municipal Accountant and BAC Chairman to require the contractor of the project Construction of Olongtao Ibaba-San Nicholas-San Vicente FMR to submit a copy of surety bond with indicated effectivity date duly certified by the issuing insurance company;
c. Municipal Accountant to ensure the refund to the concerned contractors of liquidated damages totaling P95,141.05;
d. Municipal Engineer to submit a written explanation regarding the three projects which contracts were not terminated despite incurrence of negative slippage ranging from 48.11 percent to 49.79 percent as of expiry date of contract;
e. BAC Chairman to ensure strict documentary compliance with the documentary requirements to substantiate the procurement activities of the Municipality;
f. Municipal Accountant and BAC Chairman to ensure that the surety bond submitted as warranty bond is valid for contracts with local government units and the effectivity date and duration of the bond are properly indicated therein;
g. Municipal Accountant to ensure that liquidated damages in future transactions, if any, are duly recognized and deducted before payments are made to contractors on the account of its procurement activities;
h. Municipal Engineer to closely monitor/supervise the actual accomplishments of Municipal projects to ensure that they are performed and completed as scheduled; and
i. Municipal Treasurer to ensure that the payee acknowledged the payment by affixing his signature on the Disbursement Voucher before the release of check.
We further recommended that the Municipal Mayor initiate compliance with the IRR of RA No. 9184 regarding the period of action on procurement activities and termination of contract when the project incurred negative slippage.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a. implement at once the termination of contract of this Project;
b. require the contractor to refund the remaining unrecouped advance payment of P7,384,897.05;
c. issue a Blacklisting Order disqualifying the erring contractor from participating in the bidding of all government projects;
d. forfeit the performance security posted by the contractor; and
e. impose appropriate sanctions on the consultant for the original detailed engineering design which failed to consider the conditions that led to the need for additional work costing more than 10 percent of the original total contract price.
We further recommended the Municipal Mayor to initiate strict compliance with the IMA regarding the required minimum accomplishment for the release of payments.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the: 

Municipal Treasurer to establish a Petty Cash Fund and designate Petty Cash Custodian;

Municipal Officials and Employees to stop the practice of procuring goods and services on reimbursement basis, except petty purchases to be paid out of the Petty  Cash Fund;

Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that all payments are made by check payable directly to the creditor to whom the money is due; and

Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) to strictly implement the use of any of the alternative methods of procurement provided under the Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations of R.A. 9184, if public bidding is not feasible.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor in coordination with the Sangguniang Bayan,  pass a  Sangguniang Bayan Resolution  authorizing  the  grant of mobile cellular load allowance and  internet connection taking into consideration the following:

consider the use of post-paid plan offered by telecommunication networks with monthly billing;

utilize alternative modes of communication such as internet for long-distance communication;

consider communication network offering free calls between and among networks; and

adopt and implement control measures such as setting limits and any excess on the limits set shall be for the personal account of the user;

If cell cards shall be allowed, consider purchase in bulk by the General Service Officer, following the required procurement procedures, and distribute the same in accordance with the guidelines.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
Municipal Treasurer to establish a Petty Cash Fund and designate Petty Cash Custodian;
Municipal Officials and Employees to stop the practice of  procuring goods and services on reimbursement basis, except petty purchases to be paid out of the Petty  Cash Fund;
Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that all payments are made by check payable directly to the creditor to whom the money is due; and
Bids and Awards Committee to strictly implement the use of any of the alternative methods of procurement provided under the Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations of R.A. 9184, if public bidding is not feasible.

